                <head>No. 117.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Wing</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-10-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 13, 1879</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 10th instant and its accompaniments in regard to the refusal of
                    the collector of internal revenue at San Francisco to accept as bondsmen for
                    tobacco manufacturers wealthy Chinese merchants. In reply, I beg leave to inform
                    you that the subject has been submitted to the Secretary of the Treasury, who
                    has competent jurisdiction over, affairs of that character.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, renewed assurance of my very high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
